The paper discusses open-loop transmit diversity schemes in a coded OFDM system with multiple antennas, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the decoding complexity and other features of the schemes, which could fall under systems and control (cs.SY) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper mentions the application of the discussed schemes in future wireless communication systems, which could fall under augmented reality (cs.AR).
